    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName>, <date>24 January
                1865</date></p>
            <p>To the Editor of the “Occident”</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I had the pleasure to enclose an article<lb/> translated from the
                Curacaosche Courant of the <date>24th</date> Ulto, which you will<lb/> oblige me to
                publish.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would further request you to answer me the<lb/> following
                questions either by private letter or in the “Occident” as<lb/> they refer to a case
                happening at present in our Cong:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Which do you consider of greater importance “Confirmation or<lb/>
                Calling up to the Sefer?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Can a Minister be justified in refusing to call up to the Sefer a
                lad<lb/> who has attained his religious Majority, because he has not been<lb/>
                confirmed?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">This Mr Editor is happening here, a boy who completed his<lb/> 13th
                year since <date>April 64</date> has not yet been called up, because he has<lb/> not
                been confirmed. I blame the parents who blindly submit to such<lb/> arbitrary
                decision.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am Mr Editor Your Most Obedt. Servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(3 )">
                <persName role="author">A Reformer</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Enclosed please find my card.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
